<% content_for :title, "Menu Aim" %>

<div class="content-spacing">

  <p>Menu-aim uses the <a href="https://github.com/kamens/jQuery-menu-aim" target="_blank">jQuery-menu-aim plugin</a> to create Amazon-style menu behaviours.</p>

  <p>Simply wrap your list in a div with the <code>data-menu-aim</code> attribute:</p>

  <pre class="sg-pre prettyprint">&lt;div class="menu-aim" data-menu-aim>
  &lt;ul>
    <%- (1..2).each do |i| -%>
      &lt;li>
        &lt;a href="#">Menu Item >&lt;/a>
        &lt;ul>
          <%- (1..2).each do |i| -%>
            &lt;li>&lt;a href="#">Submenu Item&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
          <%- end -%>
        &lt;/ul>
      &lt;/li>
    <%- end -%>
  &lt;/ul>
&lt;/div></pre>  

  <div class="menu-aim" data-menu-aim>
    <ul>
      <%- (1..20).each do |i| -%>
